The paper discusses the extension of a file management system for efficient storage using erasure coding, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of erasure coding also involves considerations of database systems (cs.DB) and security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the possibility of parallelizing access to distributed chunks, which relates to networked information technologies (cs.NI).
